    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This naturally aspirated engine utilizes individual throttle bodies to deliver exceptional throttle response across the power band. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M differential lock. Mechanical maintenance is up to date, including a proactive double-VANOS overhaul and a comprehensive inspection of the rear subframe reinforcement points. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative feedback and turn-in precision this chassis is renowned for. While showing minor cosmetic character consistent with its mileage, the drivetrain remains robust and the rod bearings have been monitored. This is a mechanically sound example ready for spirited canyon carving or track-day duty.",
